column5: Where is everyone going this long weekend?  As for me... Location: I'm heading back to Deseronto and try to hit those walleyes. Technique: Bottom bouncing with worm or gulp leech, and trolling crankbaits  One tip I can offer: long leads for worm harness, I'm talking like 6 feet from hook to sinker. I troll ~1.5mph
Well I gotta hit Bass Pro Saturday so I might just head up to King and try the Holland for crappie.
I'm heading to Lake Clear to find some nice Walleye on sunday and monday.
Lake Ontario hopefully for some Pike action. Will put together a report for you guys this time if i get out.

I've been fishing the last 2 days, 2- 20" Walleye & dozens of Hammer Handles I'll be working Fri, Sat & Sun but I'll be on the water Monday for sure just not sure were yet, but likely in Bruce County some were Richard
Upper French, Saturday, Sunday and Monday.
Probably Shades Mill in Cambridge on Saturday for pike and crappie.
Headed to Prince Edward County on the Lake O side at Waupoos on Monday-Friday hope to get into some eye action and toothies.
Lake Couchaching all weekend for Pike.  Have fun folks
Kam Lake, Yellowknife, NWT for Pike, Walleye and Whities.
Unfortunately I will be working and helping do the gardens for the wife.  If time permits I would like to head out to the grand for a few hrs before dark.
Fishing at BOQ with Lloyd (fishunter) on Sunday.
heading up to chandos for some pike
Was supposed to hit Rice and the area but with my bathroom in many other rooms I had to change my plans and stay home. Good thing its not Musky season opener or the bathroom would wait.
grand river in search of some hungry pike.
